{"id":"2108.08154","submitter":"Krushnachandra Panigrahy","authors":"Nirmal Chandra Rout, Krushnachandra Panigrahy, Debasisha Mishra","title":"A note on numerical ranges of tensors","comments":"20 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RA math.SP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","abstract":"  Theory of numerical range and numerical radius for tensors is not studied\nmuch in the literature. In 2016, Ke {\\it et al.} [Linear Algebra Appl., 508\n(2016) 100-132] introduced first the notion of numerical range of a tensor via\nthe $k$-mode product. However, the convexity of the numerical range via the\n$k$-mode product was not proved by them. In this paper, the notion of numerical\nrange and numerical radius for even-order square tensors using inner product\nvia the Einstein product are introduced first. We provide some sufficient\nconditions using numerical radius for a tensor to being unitary. The convexity\nof the numerical range is also proved. We also provide an algorithm to plot the\nnumerical range of a tensor. Furthermore, some properties of the numerical\nrange for the Moore--Penrose inverse of a tensor are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Aug 2021 13:56:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-19"}
